# Figma / local BMP → Connections DS

When porting icons from Figma **or** local `.bmp` files into this app, follow `.cursor/skills/figma-to-ds-assets/SKILL.md`.

## Hard rules

- **No SVG** at runtime. Do not paste SVG paths into C++.
- **Procedural first** for toolbar/control glyphs (and simple local BMPs of the same kind) using `gfx::strokeLine`, `fillRing`, `fillCircle`, `plotDisk`, `fillTriangle`, `fillRoundRect` / `roundPanel`.
- **Trace local glyph BMPs** into `draw*Icon` when the user wants procedural UI — Read the image, recipe ≤5 primitives, then code. Do not re-embed those as raster “for convenience.”
- **BMP embed only** for logos / complex fills: 8-bit Windows BMP (BI_RGB) in `data/`, drawn with `gfx::drawBmp` / `drawBmpSized`. White = transparent.
- **Scale**: Figma often 1024 → DS 256 (`×0.25`); BMPs scale ink bounds to existing toolbar glyph size (`r` ≈ 5–8). Integer layout; float pens for AA strokes.
- **Tintable icons**: `draw*Icon(cx, cy, r, u16 c)` — never bake enabled/disabled colors into geometry.
- **Palette**: map hexes / BMP ink to `gfx::pal` (`toolIcon`, `disText`, `disabled`, `submit`, …).
- **Banner**: root `icon.bmp` is ROM banner only (Makefile syncs `data/logo.bmp`) — not toolbar icons.

## Pattern

```cpp
// ✅ center + radius + color (see ui_bottom.cpp)
static void drawFooIcon(bool bottom, int cx, int cy, int r, u16 c);

// ❌ fixed color / SVG / embedding a simple glyph BMP instead of tracing it
```
